
  <div class="wrapper">

  <div id="sidebar" class="popout-sidebar">
    <%= render :partial => 'about_nav', locals: {show: 'developers'} %>
  </div>

  <div id="content" class="">
    <div class="about-block">

      <!-- ABOUT TESS DATA -->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="odd-about-block">
          <div id='code_and_data' class="h3">For Developers</div>

          TeSS is commited to the FAIR principles. Making data findable, accessible, interoperable and re-usable. As such,
          all of the content we collect in TeSS is available under the CC-BY-4.0 licence through and can be accessed
          through our API and through our widgets. The TeSS codebase is also available to re-use under the BSD Licence and can
          be found on GitHub.

          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-5 5 open-access-box">
              <div class="h2 licence-title">Software</div>
              <div class="open-access-location">
                <%= link_to 'https://github.com/ElixirTeSS/TeSS', target: '_blank' do %>
                    <div class="register-condition-graphic">
                      <%= image_tag 'about/GitHub-Mark-64px.png', class: "" %>
                    </div>
                    <div class="register-condition">The sourcecode for TeSS is available on GitHub</div>
                <% end %>
              </div>
              <div class="open-access-licence">
                <%= link_to 'https://github.com/ElixirTeSS/TeSS/blob/master/LICENSE', target: '_blank' do %>
                    <div class="register-condition-graphic"><i class="fa fa-code licence-logo"></i></div>
                    <div class="register-condition">It is available under the BSD-3 licence</div>
                <% end %>
              </div>
            </div>
              <div class="col-lg-5 open-access-box">
                <div class="h2 licence-title">Data</div>
                  <%= link_to 'https://github.com/ElixirTeSS/TeSS', target: '_blank' do %>
                    <div class="open-access-location">
                      <div class="register-condition-graphic"><i class="fa fa-plug licence-logo"></i></div>
                      <div class="register-condition">The data in TeSS can be accessed via our API</div>
                    </div>
                  <% end %>
                <div class="open-access-licence">
                  <div class="register-condition-graphic"><i class="fa fa-database licence-logo"></i></div>
                  <%= link_to 'https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/', target: '_blank' do %>
                  <div class="register-condition">It is available under the Creative Commons CC-BY 4.0 licence</div>
                  <% end %>
                </div>
              </div>
              </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="even-about-block">
          <div class="h3" id="widgets">Widgets</div>
            <p>Our widgets are chunks of javascript code that can be copied into websites to render a list of events from TeSS. There are several widget styles to choose from, which can be configured to display only events that are interesting to your community (workshops in your country, meetings about a given scientific topic, etc.).</p>
              <p>
                We have also created some javascript widgets that can be easily added to your website
                so to share training opportunities with your community.
              </p>
              <div class="widgets_guide">
                <%= link_to 'https://elixirtess.github.io/list_widget', target: '_blank' do %>
                    <%= image_tag 'about/widgets.png', class: "widgets_guide" %>
                <% end %>
              </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="odd-about-block">
          <div class="h4" id="api">API </div>

          <span style="float:right">
                      <a href="https://app.swaggerhub.com/api/njall/TeSS/1.0.0/">
                        <%= image_tag 'swagger.png', size: "50x50"%>
                      </a>
                      </span>
          <span>
                        <p>TeSS has a fully functioning JSON-API. Information about request parameters and return objects can
                        be found in our <a href="https://app.swaggerhub.com/api/njall/TeSS/1.0.0/">
                          Swagger Hub Documentation</a>
                        </p>
                        <p> As a rule of thumb - You can add .json to the end of most pages to retrieve the data in a common exchange format</p>
                      </span>
        </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</body>